1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:08,199
When did Krarok get back
from Mae Hong Son?

2
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:10,080
<i>Miss Krarok didn't go anywhere.</i>

3
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:11,120
<i>She's been in Bangkok the whole time.</i>

4
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,600
Krarok?

5
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,960
Win, you're back?

6
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:20,760
Mom…

7
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:21,960
You scum! Let go!

8
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:25,360
If you truly love my daughter,

9
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:28,640
you should know you're not ready.

10
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:31,760
You should improve yourself first
before making promises!

11
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:32,880
Let's end it here.

12
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:36,560
Can you not leave me?

13
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:40,160
Win.

14
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:43,080
Right now, you need help,
so let me help you.

15
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,160
Okay? Deal?

16
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,640
Hello. What's up?

17
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:51,800
Hey, Pie.

18
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:54,720
Have you decided
where we're treating Pun to thank him?

19
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:57,480
Anywhere is fine. You choose.

20
00:02:58,240 --> 00:03:02,160
I'm going to sleep. I'm tired.
That's all for now.

21
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:04,600
Hey, wait a minute! Don't hang up yet.

22
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,120
What?

23
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:09,440
Check your Instagram.

24
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:12,040
Pun sent you a follow request a while ago.

25
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,160
Can you accept it?

26
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:15,600
NOTIFICATIONS

27
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:20,880
PUN PARIT REQUESTED TO FOLLOW YOU

28
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:26,160
SEARCH

29
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:28,560
SAENSUK HOMESTAY

30
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:29,880
There's one.

31
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:33,360
POSTS

32
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:35,120
SAENSUK HOMESTAY MAE HONG SON

33
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:43,560
TRAINEE

34
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:57,720
WIN KAWINN

35
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,680
GOOD DAY

36
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:14,840
EVEN THOUGH I'M A PLAYBOY…

37
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:25,400
ONE TWO THREE GOAL!

38
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:34,960
<i>Did you accept Pun's follow request?</i>

39
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:41,960
PUN PARIT REQUESTED TO FOLLOW YOU

40
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:44,560
CONFIRM

41
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:47,600
FOLLOW

42
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:51,800
She's packed all her stuff and left.

43
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,480
What are you going to do now?

44
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:04,080
Be good enough for Pie.

45
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:07,400
And when that day comes…

46
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:12,400
I'll make her love me again.

47
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:31,880
<i>Pie accepted your request. Good luck.</i>

48
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:52,760
Hey, Koh.

49
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:55,120
Seriously.

50
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:58,720
Apart from your parents,
is something bothering you?

51
00:06:58,800 --> 00:06:59,680
Yes.

52
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:00,960
Is it about a girl?

53
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:09,840
It's like you found the right person

54
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:12,160
at the wrong time.

55
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:18,040
If you find the wrong person
at the right time, it's still wrong.

56
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,280
Yeah, that's true.

57
00:07:23,640 --> 00:07:30,200
Anyway, I hope my brother
finds the right person at the right time.

58
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:33,720
Then you can stop
holding on to your single life.

59
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:37,360
As for me, I'll take a break for now.

60
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:40,720
I'll see how long
you can actually take a break.

61
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:42,680
I'm serious, Pun.

62
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:46,120
This time,
I'll focus on studying and working.

63
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,800
If I'm not successful, I won't come back.

64
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:50,960
Alright.

65
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:55,520
Safe travels. Start a new life.

66
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:59,360
If you need anything,
you can call me anytime.

67
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:02,440
Thanks so much for always helping me out.

68
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:05,440
Everyone has their weak moments.

69
00:08:05,520 --> 00:08:08,160
You just have to get up quickly
after you fall.

70
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:09,840
I'm rooting for you.

71
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:14,560
Thanks so much, big bro.

72
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:16,320
Take care.

73
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,240
See you.

74
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:19,560
- Really take a break.
- I will.

75
00:08:20,760 --> 00:08:21,920
I'm leaving now.

76
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,679
Good.

77
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:35,840
Good.

78
00:08:35,919 --> 00:08:39,559
If you're angry or hate someone,
picture their face and punch.

79
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,600
One, two, three, four.

80
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:51,960
Damn.

81
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:53,320
Good.

82
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:01,360
Break time. We'll continue soon.

83
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:02,760
- Yes.
- Thank you.

84
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,520
Hey.

85
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:07,760
- What?
- Didn't you say you were tired?

86
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:11,080
With all these punches,
do you have any energy left?

87
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:12,560
Easy, no problem.

88
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:15,200
Well then, do you want to try
working on your legs next?

89
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:16,080
- Really?
- Yep.

90
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:16,880
With who?

91
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,600
- With me.
- Really? Okay.

92
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:19,680
Wait, are you serious?

93
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:20,960
- Come on.
- Come on!

94
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,600
Are you ready?

95
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:25,360
- Can you handle it?
- Come on.

96
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:28,160
Let's bring the real deal down now.

97
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:30,440
- Come on. Let's go!
- Lower it a bit.

98
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:31,720
- Go strong!
- Okay.

99
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:41,760
Pie, didn't you say you had energy?

100
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,280
What's up with you?

101
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,320
Sorry, I'm just embarrassed. It slipped.

102
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:50,720
Pie!

103
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:56,640
Hey, Pie!

104
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:59,360
- What's wrong?
- I've got a stomachache.

105
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:01,040
- A stomachache?
- It hurts so much.

106
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:03,880
- I'll go get the trainer. Hold on.
- Okay.

107
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:08,720
Auntie.

108
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:10,200
What happened, Rok?

109
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:12,080
Pie fell and has a stomachache.

110
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:13,640
I'll go get the trainer.

111
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:14,880
Hurry up, Rok.

112
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:17,160
- Pie.
- Mom.

113
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:20,920
I have a stomachache, Mom.
It hurts so much.

114
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:22,160
Really? Can you get up?

115
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,480
Come on. Get up.

116
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:25,640
Mom, I can't anymore. It hurts so much.

117
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,880
- Mom.
- Krarok! Krarok!

118
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:34,120
I'm taking Pie
to the hospital now, Krarok!

119
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,480
- Mom.
- Pie!

120
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:38,400
- My stomach hurts.
- Hang in there, Pie.

121
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:44,520
The patient is experiencing
bleeding during pregnancy.

122
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:49,120
Bleeding? Is she pregnant?

123
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:51,040
Yes.

124
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:53,960
The patient is pregnant
and has an incomplete miscarriage.

125
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:56,080
The embryo in the womb
is no longer growing.

126
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:00,880
Wait a minute, Doctor.

127
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:05,200
- My daughter is pregnant?
- Yes.

128
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:11,920
So…

129
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:15,760
So, what do we do next?

130
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:21,960
We need to do an emergency procedure
to clear all tissue from the womb.

131
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:24,000
Alright.

132
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:25,360
Hang on.

133
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:27,360
Has my child been informed of this yet?

134
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:29,400
Not yet.

135
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:31,320
Well…

136
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:33,760
Then…

137
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:38,240
I'll tell her myself.

138
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,040
Mom.

139
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,640
Have you talked to the doctor?

140
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:53,240
What did the doctor say?

141
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:03,840
Pie.

142
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:07,640
Do you remember

143
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:11,240
the day your father chose another family?

144
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:20,840
And the day I had to sign
the divorce papers…

145
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:27,040
you asked me if I was sad.

146
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:33,120
Do you remember
what I answered you that day?

147
00:12:39,640 --> 00:12:41,000
I remember.

148
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:44,600
You said that

149
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:48,880
loss and separation are normal things.

150
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:54,840
Anything that leaves our life
is something we don't need anymore.

151
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,240
That's right.

152
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,440
Anything that leaves our life

153
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:05,440
is something we don't need.

154
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:10,120
Remember that, Pie.

155
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:13,600
You must not be sad.

156
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:23,600
Mom.

157
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:27,240
What's wrong with me?

158
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,280
Pie.

159
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:38,440
You had a miscarriage.

160
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:46,400
You need to have an emergency curettage.

161
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:49,120
Right now.

162
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:55,560
Miscarriage.

163
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:16,640
Mom, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

164
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:18,360
I'm so sorry, Mom.

165
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:21,560
I'm sorry, Mom. I'm so sorry.

166
00:14:21,640 --> 00:14:24,040
- Pie, my dear.
- I'm sorry, Mom.

167
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:25,440
I'm sorry.

168
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:28,760
Pie, it's okay.

169
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:30,760
Do you know?

170
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:32,400
I'm sorry.

171
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,200
Pie.

172
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:37,800
You have to be strong.

173
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:40,760
The baby is in peace now.

174
00:14:42,560 --> 00:14:44,000
But right now,

175
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:46,960
you need to take care of yourself

176
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:49,440
and get strong.

177
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:08,040
NAGOYA, JAPAN

178
00:15:18,040 --> 00:15:19,640
<i>A double rainbow means love.</i>

179
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,320
Lovers will find their way back.

180
00:15:55,760 --> 00:15:58,280
Pie, why aren't you eating?

181
00:15:58,360 --> 00:15:59,640
Take care of yourself.

182
00:16:00,680 --> 00:16:02,240
I can't eat, Mom.

183
00:16:08,320 --> 00:16:12,320
I know this is hard,
but you need to forget about it.

184
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:16,680
Pie.

185
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:19,360
It's not your fault.

186
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:23,840
Don't blame yourself,
and don't make the same mistake again.

187
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:29,520
Hey.

188
00:16:31,480 --> 00:16:32,520
Listen to me.

189
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:35,400
No one will know about this.

190
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:38,200
And it never happened.

191
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:39,920
Understand?

192
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:46,320
Forget the bad things and start fresh.

193
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:51,080
Remember, life is meant
to be better than before.

194
00:17:15,079 --> 00:17:16,319
<i>Pie.</i>

195
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:19,000
How are you? You disappeared for a while.

196
00:17:21,319 --> 00:17:22,440
I'm okay now.

197
00:17:22,520 --> 00:17:25,400
Then let's go have dinner with Pun today.

198
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:27,440
Do you remember that he helped us?

199
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:33,920
Oh, I totally forgot about that.

200
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:36,400
How could you forget?

201
00:17:36,480 --> 00:17:38,080
Pun's been waiting for us.

202
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:39,960
He asks me about it every day.

203
00:17:40,040 --> 00:17:42,360
<i>- Got it?</i>
- Yeah.

204
00:18:17,840 --> 00:18:19,560
Hello, Rok. Have you arrived yet?

205
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:23,000
Sorry, I can't make it anymore.

206
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:25,200
What do you mean?

207
00:18:25,280 --> 00:18:27,040
My neck hurts.

208
00:18:27,120 --> 00:18:29,600
I think I slept wrong last night.

209
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,720
My mom's taking me to the doctor.

210
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:39,880
How about this?
You go have dinner with Pun. Okay?

211
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:42,920
No! Call Pun and cancel for me, Rok.

212
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:48,800
It's too late. Never mind.

213
00:18:48,880 --> 00:18:52,720
Sorry, Pie. I'll make it up to you.

214
00:18:57,600 --> 00:18:59,440
Don't think I'm a bad friend, okay?

215
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:03,120
I wish to ignite the spark of love
between you and my brother.

216
00:19:06,360 --> 00:19:08,240
- Hello, Pun.
- Hello, Pie.

217
00:19:08,320 --> 00:19:10,280
Krarok ditched us.

218
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:13,920
So, what should we do now?

219
00:19:14,520 --> 00:19:15,960
Should we reschedule?

220
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:17,880
No need to reschedule, Pie.

221
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:19,520
Since we're here, let's just eat.

222
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:21,760
Honestly, Pun.

223
00:19:21,840 --> 00:19:25,200
This restaurant is so fancy.
I'm not sure if I can treat you here.

224
00:19:25,280 --> 00:19:28,480
I don't have much money,
and I don't have a job yet.

225
00:19:29,520 --> 00:19:32,680
When you have a job, you can treat me.

226
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:33,760
Today, it's on me.

227
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:35,800
Oh no, Pun.

228
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:38,920
It's not that I don't want to pay.

229
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,880
I promised I would treat, and I will.

230
00:19:40,960 --> 00:19:43,680
I don't want to eat expensive food
and split the bill with Rok.

231
00:19:43,760 --> 00:19:45,040
I feel bad.

232
00:19:45,120 --> 00:19:47,520
If we change the place,
would you be okay with that?

233
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:49,440
Sure.

234
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:50,960
What restaurant do you want to go to?

235
00:19:56,200 --> 00:20:00,120
Oh, how's it going?
Have you decided what to eat today?

236
00:20:00,720 --> 00:20:03,800
I'll have stir-fried shrimp
with tamarind sauce.

237
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:06,600
- Okay.
- Coconut curry with lotus stem.

238
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:10,680
Fried fish with chili sauce,
steamed curry, and…

239
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:13,320
Fried chicken wings,
your favorite. How's that?

240
00:20:13,840 --> 00:20:14,760
Yes, that's good.

241
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:17,040
- Let's go with that for now, Aunt Num.
- Okay.

242
00:20:17,120 --> 00:20:18,480
What about your boyfriend?

243
00:20:18,560 --> 00:20:19,640
Would you like to add anything?

244
00:20:22,080 --> 00:20:25,720
Aunt Num, he's not my boyfriend.
He's Krarok's cousin.

245
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:27,560
Oh, you didn't tell me.

246
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:29,920
You've never brought a guy here before.

247
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,840
- Sorry about that.
- It's okay.

248
00:20:34,640 --> 00:20:36,480
- Thank you, Aunt Num.
- You're welcome.

249
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:41,960
So you've never brought a guy before?

250
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:45,120
That's true.

251
00:20:49,080 --> 00:20:52,080
Then I must be someone special.

252
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:00,920
You could say that.

253
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:15,080
Have you recommended me to Pun yet?

254
00:21:17,760 --> 00:21:20,720
Silence. Seriously, what's your problem?

255
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:22,320
Why can't you help your friend?

256
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:24,480
I really can't help you.

257
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:25,920
Why not?

258
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:29,840
Honestly, Mink.

259
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:31,560
Pun likes Pie.

260
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,400
Are you serious?

261
00:21:36,280 --> 00:21:38,120
I'm serious.

262
00:21:39,240 --> 00:21:42,400
When you told me not to get my hopes up,
was it because Pun likes Pie?

263
00:21:43,560 --> 00:21:44,800
Why didn't you tell me?

264
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:46,560
Do you still consider me a friend?

265
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:48,840
I knew that if I told you,

266
00:21:48,920 --> 00:21:51,600
you'd just be mad at me like this.

267
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:53,520
And I can't help you

268
00:21:53,600 --> 00:21:55,320
because I'm stuck in the middle.

269
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:57,000
I don't want to have problems with anyone.

270
00:21:59,440 --> 00:22:03,240
If you keep yelling at me like this,
I'm really going to go home.

271
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:06,080
Wait.

272
00:22:06,160 --> 00:22:08,320
No, this is my house.

273
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:11,120
You go home, Mink.

274
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:14,560
Go home! Here, take it. Go home now!

275
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:15,640
Hey!

276
00:22:21,320 --> 00:22:23,080
Since when did Pun like Pie?

277
00:22:24,920 --> 00:22:29,480
Probably when he helped
with the project for Professor Phupha.

278
00:22:30,840 --> 00:22:32,760
Then why didn't he tell me?

279
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:35,040
Why would he tell you?

280
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:37,280
I don't understand.

281
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:39,760
Why does Pie take everything from me?

282
00:22:39,840 --> 00:22:43,480
Since freshman year, I wanted to be
head cheerleader, but she got it.

283
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:46,200
In the faculty beauty contest,
her scores beat mine.

284
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:49,000
Even the cheer president position
I worked hard for.

285
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:51,600
But after my accident
and months in the hospital,

286
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:54,280
- it went to her.
- Stop it, Mink.

287
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:56,440
Why are you whining to me?

288
00:22:56,520 --> 00:22:57,760
I want you to know

289
00:22:57,840 --> 00:23:01,600
that your sweet Pie
is actually trying to beat me.

290
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:04,600
She's trying to take
everything that's mine, even you.

291
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:07,960
What's this got to do with it?

292
00:23:08,040 --> 00:23:09,440
It has everything to do with it.

293
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:12,240
You and I have been together
since grade seven.

294
00:23:12,320 --> 00:23:13,480
We were super close.

295
00:23:13,560 --> 00:23:15,280
Then Pie came into your life.

296
00:23:15,360 --> 00:23:17,240
Now you're close to her.

297
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:22,800
Hey, Mink.

298
00:23:23,320 --> 00:23:25,600
You're overthinking this.

299
00:23:26,280 --> 00:23:28,080
I'm still close to you, you know.

300
00:23:28,160 --> 00:23:31,520
The only reason you're still close to me
is because I haven't let you go.

301
00:23:38,080 --> 00:23:39,280
I don't care.

302
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:42,560
Pie may have beaten me at a lot of things,

303
00:23:42,640 --> 00:23:44,440
but not with Pun.

304
00:23:45,040 --> 00:23:46,480
This is about my pride.

305
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:51,320
In the end, Pun may not choose me,

306
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:52,760
but he shouldn't choose her either.

307
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:07,600
- Pie.
- Yes?

308
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:10,840
Can I ask you something personal?

309
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:16,920
Sure. What would you like to know?

310
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:19,440
Where is your dad?

311
00:24:19,520 --> 00:24:21,120
Why do I only see your mom?

312
00:24:23,240 --> 00:24:24,800
My parents got divorced.

313
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:27,720
When I was in middle school,

314
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:30,760
my dad started a new family,
and we haven't been in touch since.

315
00:24:30,840 --> 00:24:33,400
I live with my mom now,
just the two of us.

316
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:38,280
You seem to have handled
your parents' divorce really well.

317
00:24:38,800 --> 00:24:41,960
Pun, I didn't handle it well at all.

318
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:43,480
I just accepted the truth.

319
00:24:45,320 --> 00:24:49,280
If someone decides to leave,
how can we stop them?

320
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:52,800
Even without him,

321
00:24:54,320 --> 00:24:55,880
we still have to move on and live.

322
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:08,240
What's this?

323
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:10,760
Sorry.

324
00:25:10,840 --> 00:25:12,120
- It's okay.
- It's alright.

325
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:13,520
Go play over there.

326
00:25:17,080 --> 00:25:18,080
Do you like kids?

327
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:21,400
Yes, I do.

328
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:23,440
I like them too.

329
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:28,320
If you have a family,
would you want to have kids?

330
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:31,600
Well…

331
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:34,720
Yes, I would.

332
00:25:36,280 --> 00:25:37,320
I would too.

333
00:25:38,600 --> 00:25:42,360
If I get married,
I plan to have kids right away.

334
00:25:42,880 --> 00:25:45,920
Because when the kids grow up,
we won't be too old.

335
00:25:47,160 --> 00:25:49,480
Pun, you're thinking way ahead.

336
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:50,800
I have to think about it.

337
00:25:51,560 --> 00:25:54,560
I'm getting older,
so I have to plan for things.

338
00:25:55,280 --> 00:25:56,400
Yes.

339
00:25:57,040 --> 00:26:01,640
For me, the only plan right now
is finding a job quickly.

340
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:03,920
Nothing else is on my mind.

341
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:07,240
Have you decided on a job?

342
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:10,880
One moment.

343
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:13,520
MOM

344
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:16,560
I forgot to tell Mom
we changed restaurants.

345
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:18,280
Sorry, Pun.

346
00:26:18,800 --> 00:26:21,240
Hello, Mom. I forgot to tell you
we changed restaurants.

347
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:23,040
How could you forget something important?

348
00:26:23,120 --> 00:26:25,040
I'm already at the restaurant.

349
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:28,120
I'm sorry, Mom. It was last minute.

350
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:30,120
I totally forgot. I'll go home by myself.

351
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:31,320
No need.

352
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:33,400
Just tell me the restaurant,
I'll come pick you up.

353
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:36,000
Should I talk to her?

354
00:26:36,080 --> 00:26:38,400
Who's that in the background, Pie?

355
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:46,040
Hello, ma'am. I'm Pun, Krarok's brother.

356
00:26:46,120 --> 00:26:48,520
<i>We met when I went to apologize</i>
<i>to you at your house.</i>

357
00:26:49,360 --> 00:26:52,400
Right now, Pie and I
moved to a different restaurant.

358
00:26:52,480 --> 00:26:55,560
I'm sorry
that we didn't inform you beforehand.

359
00:26:56,080 --> 00:26:58,520
I'll take responsibility
by driving her home.

360
00:26:58,600 --> 00:27:00,000
Pun, it's okay.

361
00:27:00,080 --> 00:27:03,000
It's alright. I'll pick her up myself.

362
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:05,800
The traffic is really bad.
I think it'll take at least an hour.

363
00:27:05,880 --> 00:27:08,400
I promise I'll get her home
as quickly as I can.

364
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:13,160
Alright then. Just hurry up like you said.

365
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:15,680
I will. Goodbye.

366
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:20,320
Everything's set.

367
00:27:21,080 --> 00:27:22,600
Thank you, Pun.

368
00:27:24,520 --> 00:27:25,960
Let's go. I'll take you.

369
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:27,520
Okay.

370
00:27:37,200 --> 00:27:41,280
- I'm here! No need for the doorbell.
- Hello, Mom.

371
00:27:42,040 --> 00:27:43,240
Hello, ma'am.

372
00:27:43,320 --> 00:27:44,760
What's with calling me that?

373
00:27:44,840 --> 00:27:46,040
You can just call me Mom.

374
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:49,480
Thank you so much for bringing Pie home.

375
00:27:50,480 --> 00:27:51,360
It's my pleasure.

376
00:27:52,520 --> 00:27:53,680
You must be tired.

377
00:27:53,760 --> 00:27:55,520
Come in for some cold water.

378
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:57,200
- Come on, come in.
- Mom, it's okay.

379
00:27:58,560 --> 00:27:59,720
I mean…

380
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:02,280
Let Pun go rest.

381
00:28:02,360 --> 00:28:04,560
Pie, you're being rude.

382
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:06,200
It sounds like you're chasing him away.

383
00:28:06,280 --> 00:28:07,440
Not at all.

384
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:09,080
I can't stay today.

385
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:11,360
I need to head back.
I hope to catch up next time.

386
00:28:11,440 --> 00:28:13,480
- Alright then. Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

387
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:15,040
Thank you, Pun. Goodbye.

388
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:16,880
- See you later, Pie.
- Yes.

389
00:28:17,720 --> 00:28:20,000
Come visit again soon, whenever you can.

390
00:28:20,080 --> 00:28:21,800
- Thank you.
- Drive safely.

391
00:28:22,960 --> 00:28:24,960
Oh my goodness.

392
00:28:25,720 --> 00:28:27,360
Drive carefully!

393
00:28:32,640 --> 00:28:34,040
- Mom.
- Yes?

394
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:36,040
Are you thinking about something?

395
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:39,240
What are you thinking about?

396
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:41,040
Why did you try to chase him away?

397
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:43,640
He made the effort to drive you home.

398
00:28:44,240 --> 00:28:46,720
Pie, let me ask you directly.

399
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:48,840
Is he interested in you?

400
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:52,920
- No, Mom.
- What?

401
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:55,800
He took you out for dinner
and drove you home.

402
00:28:55,880 --> 00:28:58,320
It's pretty obvious
he's interested in you.

403
00:28:58,840 --> 00:29:03,040
If he is interested in you,
just say yes, okay?

404
00:29:03,120 --> 00:29:04,920
This one gets my approval.

405
00:29:05,520 --> 00:29:07,680
Mom, that's a bit fast.

406
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:10,800
I've already done my research.

407
00:29:10,880 --> 00:29:13,880
Pun is well-mannered,
comes from a good family.

408
00:29:13,960 --> 00:29:17,280
Education, background,
he has everything you could ask for.

409
00:29:17,360 --> 00:29:19,120
If you get him as your boyfriend,

410
00:29:19,200 --> 00:29:21,680
you'll be set for life, Pie.

411
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:24,280
Mom, you're thinking way ahead.

412
00:29:24,360 --> 00:29:26,040
There's nothing going on yet.

413
00:29:26,600 --> 00:29:28,760
Pun has a lot of people interested in him.

414
00:29:28,840 --> 00:29:30,360
He's not interested in me.

415
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:34,040
A lot of people liking him is no problem.

416
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:40,120
If he likes you, that's all that matters.

417
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:41,880
Remember that, Pie.

418
00:29:53,880 --> 00:29:56,520
Mink is the niece of my close friend.

419
00:29:56,600 --> 00:29:57,840
She just graduated.

420
00:29:58,640 --> 00:30:00,960
She said you taught her, right?

421
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:03,280
Yes.

422
00:30:03,360 --> 00:30:05,000
That means you already know each other.

423
00:30:05,600 --> 00:30:07,200
Yes, ma'am.

424
00:30:07,280 --> 00:30:09,760
Mink still doesn't have a job anywhere.

425
00:30:09,840 --> 00:30:12,920
I was thinking of letting her
come help out at the company.

426
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:14,440
But you know Pun's personality.

427
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:16,960
He rarely believes what I say.

428
00:30:17,040 --> 00:30:18,920
If you're the one who says it,
he'll listen.

429
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:21,800
So I'll leave it to you
to handle this for me.

430
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:24,400
Of course.

431
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:30,320
Our company has come this far
thanks to your support.

432
00:30:30,920 --> 00:30:33,400
Since you personally asked like this,

433
00:30:33,480 --> 00:30:35,960
how could I possibly refuse?

434
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:39,280
If you're confident that Mink
can really help our company,

435
00:30:39,360 --> 00:30:43,320
then I'm happy to hire her.

436
00:30:43,400 --> 00:30:45,600
Thank you so much, Phu.

437
00:30:46,640 --> 00:30:48,520
But don't tell Pun about this yet.

438
00:30:49,120 --> 00:30:50,080
You sure about that?

439
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:51,840
Telling him now will cause trouble.

440
00:30:51,920 --> 00:30:55,080
Once Pun sees Mink working here,
he'll understand on his own.

441
00:30:55,160 --> 00:30:57,280
Oh, I see.

442
00:30:57,360 --> 00:31:00,680
- I'll do my best at work, Professor.
- Alright.

443
00:31:01,720 --> 00:31:03,080
I'll be watching.

444
00:31:03,680 --> 00:31:06,600
Anyway, I should get going now.

445
00:31:06,680 --> 00:31:09,320
I have to get back to the university.
I have papers to check.

446
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:10,840
Goodbye.

447
00:31:11,480 --> 00:31:12,480
Goodbye.

448
00:31:15,920 --> 00:31:21,880
For this year, the most outstanding
and complete thesis is this one.

449
00:31:21,960 --> 00:31:28,000
"Huay Tong Kor Karen Textiles",
by Phitpicha Attwijit.

450
00:31:28,080 --> 00:31:29,840
Let's give her a round of applause.

451
00:31:31,080 --> 00:31:32,760
Very impressive.

452
00:31:43,120 --> 00:31:44,320
You look amazing.

453
00:31:50,480 --> 00:31:52,000
Pie.

454
00:31:52,080 --> 00:31:55,280
Everyone's happy for you.
What's with that face?

455
00:31:56,600 --> 00:31:58,880
I am happy.

456
00:31:59,480 --> 00:32:00,840
That's happy?

457
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:04,080
See? I'm smiling.

458
00:32:18,840 --> 00:32:21,880
Congrats on beating me again.

459
00:32:22,800 --> 00:32:24,160
I never tried to beat you.

460
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:25,720
I just did my assignment.

461
00:32:27,080 --> 00:32:28,400
Always acting like the heroine.

462
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:30,160
Doesn't it get tiring?

463
00:32:31,520 --> 00:32:35,520
Just so you know, you'll never be perfect,
no matter how hard you try.

464
00:32:35,600 --> 00:32:37,520
I've never thought I was perfect.

465
00:32:37,600 --> 00:32:40,360
- No one in this world is.
- There is. Me.

466
00:32:41,080 --> 00:32:43,520
I have everything everyone wants.

467
00:32:43,600 --> 00:32:46,920
And everything you don't.

468
00:32:48,240 --> 00:32:51,560
I know what your family is really like.

469
00:32:52,360 --> 00:32:55,360
I just kept quiet.
Didn't want to stab you in the back.

470
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:56,840
Go ahead and say it.

471
00:32:56,920 --> 00:32:59,280
I won't be mad. It's the truth.

472
00:32:59,360 --> 00:33:01,400
But stop with the drama.

473
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:03,480
Just say what you want. Get to the point.

474
00:33:03,560 --> 00:33:04,920
What do you want?

475
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:08,360
Rok told me that Pun likes you.

476
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:12,960
Pun likes me?

477
00:33:13,880 --> 00:33:16,080
You really didn't know?
Or are you pretending?

478
00:33:16,840 --> 00:33:20,200
So what? Rok told you,
and you came here to yell at me?

479
00:33:20,720 --> 00:33:22,360
Oh, you and Pun?

480
00:33:22,440 --> 00:33:24,560
Yeah. I like him.

481
00:33:24,640 --> 00:33:27,160
If you're really not interested, back off.

482
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:29,240
I'm serious about him.

483
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:34,720
But if you want to compete with me,
then bring it on.

484
00:33:49,680 --> 00:33:52,040
Pie! Pie!

485
00:33:52,120 --> 00:33:54,200
- Wait!
- What is it?

486
00:33:54,280 --> 00:33:56,400
Pun invited us to lunch. Come with us.

487
00:33:57,080 --> 00:33:59,240
I can't, sorry.
My mom's here to pick me up.

488
00:33:59,320 --> 00:34:00,480
I'll see you later.

489
00:34:00,560 --> 00:34:03,160
- Hold on, Pie…
- See you. Bye.

490
00:34:05,080 --> 00:34:06,880
Well.

491
00:34:16,639 --> 00:34:18,600
HUAY TONG KOR KAREN TEXTILES

492
00:34:54,920 --> 00:34:56,199
Hello, Pun.

493
00:34:56,719 --> 00:34:57,720
<i>Pie.</i>

494
00:34:58,400 --> 00:35:00,920
<i>There's something</i>
<i>I want to talk to you about right now.</i>

495
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:04,360
I'm already home.
I can't really go out now.

496
00:35:04,880 --> 00:35:06,800
<i>Just step outside.</i>

497
00:35:07,400 --> 00:35:08,400
I'm right in front of your house.

498
00:35:08,480 --> 00:35:10,800
What? In front of my house?

499
00:35:11,720 --> 00:35:13,040
I brought this back for you.

500
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:17,360
Did you forget it, or leave it on purpose?

501
00:35:17,440 --> 00:35:20,040
The project's finished,
so I didn't want to keep it.

502
00:35:21,320 --> 00:35:22,520
Pie.

503
00:35:23,120 --> 00:35:25,000
That's a shame. I read the whole thing.

504
00:35:25,080 --> 00:35:27,040
It's very detailed.

505
00:35:27,120 --> 00:35:29,680
Well researched,
but easy to read. I like it.

506
00:35:30,280 --> 00:35:31,320
Thank you.

507
00:35:32,760 --> 00:35:36,480
If you don't want it, can I keep it?

508
00:35:37,680 --> 00:35:39,920
Sure. That's up to you.

509
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:44,160
Pie, is something wrong?

510
00:35:45,240 --> 00:35:47,960
You seem different today.

511
00:35:48,040 --> 00:35:50,080
Is something bothering you?

512
00:35:53,280 --> 00:35:54,560
Is it about me?

513
00:36:01,240 --> 00:36:02,600
Did you tell Rok

514
00:36:03,880 --> 00:36:05,760
that you like me?

515
00:36:14,480 --> 00:36:16,040
MADAM

516
00:36:19,200 --> 00:36:20,360
Yes.

517
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:24,120
I told Rok I like you.

518
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:30,400
Pie.

519
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:34,000
Don't go quiet like that. Well…

520
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:37,320
Now I don't know what to say next.

521
00:36:38,400 --> 00:36:41,760
Thank you so much, Pun. But…

522
00:36:42,840 --> 00:36:43,760
"But…"

523
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:47,960
That doesn't sound good.

524
00:36:50,840 --> 00:36:54,840
But you don't really know me yet.

525
00:36:55,440 --> 00:36:59,640
If you knew me better,
you might not like me anymore.

526
00:37:02,280 --> 00:37:07,240
Do you know when you truly know someone?

527
00:37:10,200 --> 00:37:11,760
When they don't know you're watching.

528
00:37:13,880 --> 00:37:16,400
I've been observing you,

529
00:37:16,480 --> 00:37:21,320
getting to know the real you
when you didn't know.

530
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:26,000
From the first time we met.

531
00:37:27,280 --> 00:37:29,320
When you're with Rok.

532
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:31,000
When you're with your mom.

533
00:37:32,480 --> 00:37:35,120
When you're around other people.

534
00:37:36,160 --> 00:37:38,560
The way you treat them.

535
00:37:39,720 --> 00:37:40,920
That's it.

536
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:43,720
It shows who you really are.

537
00:37:49,720 --> 00:37:50,920
That's the Pie I like.

538
00:37:54,600 --> 00:37:56,160
Yes!

539
00:37:57,040 --> 00:37:58,320
Pie!

540
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:04,520
I guess that sounded a bit over the top.

541
00:38:05,120 --> 00:38:06,120
You're speechless.

542
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:08,120
No, it's just…

543
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:13,640
Pun, thank you so much.

544
00:38:14,680 --> 00:38:17,200
I really don't know what to say.

545
00:38:19,680 --> 00:38:20,800
Then,

546
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:23,280
you don't have to say anything yet.

547
00:38:26,120 --> 00:38:27,800
But you can come work for me instead.

548
00:38:27,880 --> 00:38:29,000
Huh?

549
00:38:29,080 --> 00:38:30,200
What job?

550
00:38:30,280 --> 00:38:33,800
I started a company that designs
and builds museums.

551
00:38:33,880 --> 00:38:38,160
I need someone to handle research
on textiles and folk culture.

552
00:38:38,240 --> 00:38:41,960
After seeing your work, I really liked it.

553
00:38:42,040 --> 00:38:43,880
I think you'd do a great job.

554
00:38:44,400 --> 00:38:45,760
Come work with me.

555
00:38:47,520 --> 00:38:51,640
And don't worry,
I didn't choose you for personal reasons.

556
00:38:52,240 --> 00:38:55,160
I chose you because of your work.

557
00:38:55,960 --> 00:38:57,200
Let's work together.

558
00:39:03,360 --> 00:39:06,360
Let me think about it first.

559
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:10,080
Pie, what are you doing?

560
00:39:10,160 --> 00:39:12,640
This isn't how it's supposed to go!

561
00:39:13,760 --> 00:39:15,040
I'll wait for your answer.

562
00:39:17,040 --> 00:39:20,400
Anyway, I'm not pressuring you.

563
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:23,480
But I don't like being disappointed.

564
00:39:27,600 --> 00:39:29,200
Don't let me down.

565
00:39:34,120 --> 00:39:35,600
I'll try.

566
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:40,360
Why aren't you going to work with Pun?

567
00:39:40,440 --> 00:39:42,600
What's there to think about, Pie?

568
00:39:44,520 --> 00:39:46,280
You don't want me to get a job.

569
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:47,720
You want me to get a boyfriend.

570
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:49,400
You heard everything, didn't you?

571
00:39:49,480 --> 00:39:52,600
Yeah, and it really bothers me.

572
00:39:52,680 --> 00:39:54,840
Why act so hard to get?

573
00:39:54,920 --> 00:39:58,520
But with someone unworthy,
you throw yourself at them.

574
00:40:03,400 --> 00:40:08,440
I mean the reason I'm pushing for Pun
is because he's perfect.

575
00:40:08,520 --> 00:40:11,840
Looks, work, wealth.

576
00:40:11,920 --> 00:40:13,880
He's got it all, Pie.

577
00:40:13,960 --> 00:40:18,120
If you're with him, it'll be a blessing.

578
00:40:18,880 --> 00:40:22,360
- Mom, I don't want to…
- Okay.

579
00:40:22,440 --> 00:40:26,680
If you're not ready to think about love,

580
00:40:27,200 --> 00:40:28,880
how about work?

581
00:40:28,960 --> 00:40:31,040
Why don't you try working with him?

582
00:40:31,120 --> 00:40:33,560
If you don't like it, quit.

583
00:40:33,640 --> 00:40:36,760
If you work with him,
it'll give you experience.

584
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:41,200
Plus, you'll earn money for the family.

585
00:40:42,240 --> 00:40:44,040
Mom, I've told you…

586
00:40:44,120 --> 00:40:46,280
Call Pun now. Okay?

587
00:40:46,360 --> 00:40:49,640
- Mom, I don't want to…
- Do you want me to call him?

588
00:40:52,200 --> 00:40:53,480
Mom.

589
00:40:53,560 --> 00:40:57,840
Please, no. I'll call him myself.

590
00:40:58,440 --> 00:40:59,800
You really need to call him.

591
00:41:01,400 --> 00:41:02,640
Okay.

592
00:41:04,200 --> 00:41:06,520
- Are you going to work with Pun?
- Yeah.

593
00:41:06,600 --> 00:41:08,760
I'm going to be his secretary too.

594
00:41:08,840 --> 00:41:10,240
- Really?
- Yeah.

595
00:41:11,120 --> 00:41:14,600
His secretary just quit,
so he's having me fill in.

596
00:41:14,680 --> 00:41:16,160
No way!

597
00:41:16,240 --> 00:41:20,000
I thought my first job
would be all alone and boring.

598
00:41:20,080 --> 00:41:21,880
I'm so glad I'll be working with you!

599
00:41:21,960 --> 00:41:23,720
Hey, I'm happy too!

600
00:41:24,320 --> 00:41:26,080
Let's give it our best.

601
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:28,520
- Hang on!
- What?

602
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:31,720
Cheers to our first job together.

603
00:41:32,960 --> 00:41:34,440
- Yay!
- Cheers!

604
00:41:38,240 --> 00:41:39,440
- How is it?
- So good!

605
00:41:39,520 --> 00:41:40,480
- Really?
- Yeah.

606
00:41:40,560 --> 00:41:42,680
- Eat up.
- So good!

607
00:41:46,360 --> 00:41:47,440
- Rok.
- What?

608
00:41:47,960 --> 00:41:50,960
Pun confessed to me

609
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:52,880
that he likes me.

610
00:41:55,800 --> 00:41:57,120
What?

611
00:41:57,200 --> 00:42:00,400
Really? Pun confessed to you?

612
00:42:00,480 --> 00:42:02,640
Seriously, Pie?

613
00:42:02,720 --> 00:42:03,880
- No way! Oh my God!
- Hey!

614
00:42:03,960 --> 00:42:06,040
Stop acting so surprised.

615
00:42:06,120 --> 00:42:09,000
You already knew. No need to pretend.

616
00:42:09,080 --> 00:42:10,520
How did you know I knew?

617
00:42:11,560 --> 00:42:12,720
Mink told me.

618
00:42:12,800 --> 00:42:14,680
- What?
- Yeah.

619
00:42:15,480 --> 00:42:18,320
She told me she likes Pun too.

620
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:22,440
And she declared war.
If I get involved, I'd have to fight her.

621
00:42:22,520 --> 00:42:24,080
- So I told her--
- Stop right there!

622
00:42:24,160 --> 00:42:25,160
What?

623
00:42:25,680 --> 00:42:28,280
Don't even think about backing down.

624
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:33,320
The one who decides who to choose
isn't you, it's my brother.

625
00:42:34,080 --> 00:42:36,360
But I don't want any drama.

626
00:42:36,440 --> 00:42:37,520
Trust me.

627
00:42:37,600 --> 00:42:41,040
The more you run, the more Pun will chase.

628
00:42:41,120 --> 00:42:44,360
If he doesn't back off,
Mink will get even crazier.

629
00:42:44,440 --> 00:42:46,640
And the one who'll suffer is you.

630
00:42:47,240 --> 00:42:48,880
So what do you want me to do?

631
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:52,880
Do you get it? I don't want drama.

632
00:42:53,480 --> 00:42:57,320
I just want to work,
support my mom and family,

633
00:42:57,400 --> 00:42:58,640
and improve my life.

634
00:42:58,720 --> 00:42:59,800
That's it.

635
00:42:59,880 --> 00:43:02,040
Yeah, just do that.

636
00:43:02,120 --> 00:43:05,720
Work hard, and don't worry about Mink.

637
00:43:05,800 --> 00:43:07,880
She won't stay upset long.

638
00:43:07,960 --> 00:43:12,040
If something makes her life tough,
she'll stop.

639
00:43:12,120 --> 00:43:14,160
Don't worry, just trust me.

640
00:43:21,240 --> 00:43:24,320
Alright, I'll show you
around the different departments.

641
00:43:24,400 --> 00:43:27,280
Okay. But I have one question.

642
00:43:28,000 --> 00:43:29,040
What's that?

643
00:43:29,120 --> 00:43:32,360
Since I've graduated,
can I just call you by your name?

644
00:43:34,760 --> 00:43:37,200
Sure. Whatever makes you comfortable.

645
00:43:38,000 --> 00:43:39,880
- Thank you, Phu.
- Yeah.

646
00:43:39,960 --> 00:43:41,920
I need to use the bathroom.
I'll be right back.

647
00:43:42,640 --> 00:43:44,400
Take your time. Go ahead.

648
00:43:44,480 --> 00:43:45,960
Which way is the bathroom?

649
00:43:46,040 --> 00:43:48,280
Just go straight and turn left.

650
00:43:48,360 --> 00:43:50,400
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

651
00:43:52,880 --> 00:43:56,280
First day at work
and wearing a skirt this short.

652
00:44:01,440 --> 00:44:03,920
Mink, how did you get here?

653
00:44:04,440 --> 00:44:06,160
I'm here to work with you, of course.

654
00:44:06,240 --> 00:44:07,480
Surprised?

655
00:44:10,560 --> 00:44:13,080
Could you not surprise me this much?

656
00:44:13,160 --> 00:44:17,080
I'm just happy!
We're finally working together.

657
00:44:17,800 --> 00:44:19,040
Well…

658
00:44:19,640 --> 00:44:21,640
It's not just the two of us, though.

659
00:44:30,800 --> 00:44:32,680
Surprised?

660
00:44:33,480 --> 00:44:34,720
What are you doing here?

661
00:44:35,760 --> 00:44:37,400
I'm here to be Pun's assistant.

662
00:44:38,880 --> 00:44:41,400
Why are there so many surprises today?

663
00:44:41,480 --> 00:44:43,720
Oh no, Rok.

664
00:44:47,640 --> 00:44:49,600
Hey, Pun! Good to see you.

665
00:44:49,680 --> 00:44:51,280
I need to tell you something.

666
00:44:52,240 --> 00:44:53,080
What is it?

667
00:44:53,160 --> 00:44:57,320
The other day, your mom sent me
a new employee to work with us.

668
00:44:57,400 --> 00:44:58,880
She started today.

669
00:45:00,000 --> 00:45:00,960
Why are you telling me now?

670
00:45:01,040 --> 00:45:02,200
Well…

671
00:45:02,280 --> 00:45:04,760
She told me not to tell you.

672
00:45:04,840 --> 00:45:08,040
I'm just a small shareholder,
I can't oppose her.

673
00:45:08,120 --> 00:45:10,560
She said she's the niece
of a friend or something.

674
00:45:10,640 --> 00:45:13,880
Wait, don't tell me
it's Mungmink, your student?

675
00:45:13,960 --> 00:45:16,160
Hello, Pun!

676
00:45:17,480 --> 00:45:20,000
I'm so happy we're going to work together.

677
00:45:20,080 --> 00:45:22,520
I'm super excited to work with Rok too.

678
00:45:22,600 --> 00:45:24,040
It's going to be so much fun.

679
00:45:24,120 --> 00:45:25,400
Wait.

680
00:45:25,480 --> 00:45:28,440
Aren't you happy to work with Pie too?

681
00:45:28,520 --> 00:45:30,080
You two were in the same class.

682
00:45:31,840 --> 00:45:33,400
Pie and I aren't really close.

683
00:45:34,040 --> 00:45:36,640
But Rok and I have been classmates
since we were kids.

684
00:45:36,720 --> 00:45:40,280
I always talk to her about everything,
so I'm extra happy about this.

685
00:45:40,360 --> 00:45:41,440
I see.

686
00:45:41,520 --> 00:45:42,960
As for Pie…

687
00:45:44,840 --> 00:45:47,680
I'm sure we'll get closer
once we know each other better.

688
00:45:48,320 --> 00:45:50,600
Of course, take your time.

689
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:55,240
Well…

690
00:45:55,320 --> 00:45:57,720
I was planning to give Rok
and Pie a tour of the office.

691
00:45:58,360 --> 00:46:00,160
Since you're showing Mungmink around,

692
00:46:00,680 --> 00:46:01,880
can you take care of Rok and Pie?

693
00:46:01,960 --> 00:46:03,920
Aren't you going with us, Pun?

694
00:46:04,000 --> 00:46:05,360
I have other work to do.

695
00:46:06,120 --> 00:46:09,640
Showing the new employees around
doesn't need two people.

696
00:46:10,320 --> 00:46:11,280
I'm counting on you.

697
00:46:19,000 --> 00:46:20,440
Well…

698
00:46:20,520 --> 00:46:23,280
If that's the case, I'm Professor…

699
00:46:23,880 --> 00:46:27,520
Oops, call me Phupha,
or whatever you like.

700
00:46:27,600 --> 00:46:29,320
I'll be the one to show you around.

701
00:46:29,400 --> 00:46:30,800
Let's go. Follow me.

702
00:46:37,560 --> 00:46:38,800
Oh no.

703
00:46:38,880 --> 00:46:41,440
I thought work would be peaceful.

704
00:46:41,520 --> 00:46:43,920
What's this? I have to play peacemaker
between you and Mink?

705
00:46:44,800 --> 00:46:45,840
Let's go.

706
00:46:48,000 --> 00:46:52,000
This will be the department where we work.

707
00:46:52,080 --> 00:46:53,520
Wow.

708
00:46:57,240 --> 00:46:58,200
Alright.

709
00:46:58,280 --> 00:47:01,640
This is Pun's secretary desk.

710
00:47:01,720 --> 00:47:03,760
This desk is a bit unlucky.

711
00:47:03,840 --> 00:47:06,520
If your luck isn't strong,
you won't pass probation.

712
00:47:06,600 --> 00:47:10,440
But if your luck is a bit better,
you'll pass probation, but not for long.

713
00:47:11,480 --> 00:47:13,040
However, Rok,

714
00:47:13,120 --> 00:47:17,400
you might be exempt
since you're Pun's close cousin.

715
00:47:17,480 --> 00:47:18,480
Good luck.

716
00:47:19,640 --> 00:47:21,040
- I'll do my best!
- Great.

717
00:47:21,560 --> 00:47:25,600
As for Mink and Pie,
you'll sit together at this desk for now.

718
00:47:29,640 --> 00:47:31,920
Is it okay if you sit together?

719
00:47:32,840 --> 00:47:35,080
Sure, no problem.

720
00:47:36,280 --> 00:47:37,560
I'm an easygoing person.

721
00:47:41,720 --> 00:47:43,080
I can sit anywhere.

722
00:47:46,600 --> 00:47:49,160
I'll go back to teaching now.

723
00:47:49,240 --> 00:47:50,200
Alright.

724
00:47:50,280 --> 00:47:51,400
- Feel free to settle in.
- See you, Professor.

725
00:47:51,480 --> 00:47:52,600
- Goodbye.
- Thank you.

726
00:48:04,640 --> 00:48:05,840
- Hey.
- Huh?

727
00:48:05,920 --> 00:48:07,160
Answer the phone, Secretary.

728
00:48:07,240 --> 00:48:08,160
- Me?
- Yeah.

729
00:48:08,240 --> 00:48:09,440
Oh, right.

730
00:48:09,520 --> 00:48:10,920
Answer the phone.

731
00:48:15,360 --> 00:48:16,680
Hello, this is Khun Pun's office.

732
00:48:16,760 --> 00:48:18,800
Krarok, Mr. Pun's secretary, speaking.

733
00:48:19,600 --> 00:48:23,120
<i>Rok, it's an internal call.</i>
<i>No need to be so formal.</i>

734
00:48:23,200 --> 00:48:25,480
If the light is on at line one, that's me.

735
00:48:26,480 --> 00:48:28,160
Got it, Pun.

736
00:48:28,240 --> 00:48:30,040
What do you need me to do?

737
00:48:31,200 --> 00:48:32,040
Okay.

738
00:48:32,120 --> 00:48:34,440
Hang on.

739
00:48:34,520 --> 00:48:35,760
How does he like his coffee?

740
00:48:35,840 --> 00:48:39,800
He told me to make him coffee and hung up.

741
00:48:39,880 --> 00:48:44,040
Do you think he'll get mad if I ask
after he finishes talking to the client?

742
00:48:44,120 --> 00:48:46,440
Hot Americano, half shot of syrup,
and a cup of hot water.

743
00:48:47,600 --> 00:48:48,840
How do you know that?

744
00:48:48,920 --> 00:48:50,600
We had lunch together before.

745
00:48:50,680 --> 00:48:52,680
Pun ordered it that way, so I remembered.

746
00:48:54,640 --> 00:48:57,160
But the light's different now.
This is an outside line.

747
00:48:57,240 --> 00:48:59,280
Hey, can you make the coffee for Pun?

748
00:48:59,360 --> 00:49:03,040
He said to leave it in the meeting room.
Please, can you do that for me?

749
00:49:04,200 --> 00:49:06,480
Hello, this is Khun Pun's office.

750
00:49:06,560 --> 00:49:08,840
Krarok, Mr. Pun's secretary, speaking.

751
00:49:28,680 --> 00:49:30,560
Oh no!

752
00:49:31,560 --> 00:49:32,600
Shoot!

753
00:49:32,680 --> 00:49:33,840
My project!

754
00:49:33,920 --> 00:49:35,640
Oh no!

755
00:49:37,000 --> 00:49:39,040
- I'm sorry!
- It's all wet.

756
00:49:39,120 --> 00:49:42,040
Are you okay? Is there any pain?
Let me clean it up for you.

757
00:49:42,120 --> 00:49:45,000
No, I'm fine. But my work is ruined.

758
00:49:45,080 --> 00:49:47,440
- Hold on a second.
- It's due this afternoon.

759
00:49:48,560 --> 00:49:49,440
What should I do?

760
00:49:49,520 --> 00:49:50,600
Let me clean it up for you.

761
00:49:50,680 --> 00:49:53,920
- Sorry!
- This isn't going to work.

762
00:49:56,520 --> 00:49:57,600
Let me check the file.

763
00:49:57,680 --> 00:49:58,840
Is it there?

764
00:49:59,360 --> 00:50:00,360
Pie!

765
00:50:01,360 --> 00:50:04,440
Help her out. I'll make
a new cup of coffee for Pun.

766
00:50:12,880 --> 00:50:13,880
Is it okay?

767
00:50:15,520 --> 00:50:17,520
But how do we print it now?

768
00:50:24,080 --> 00:50:25,920
The coffee's ready, Pun.

769
00:50:32,080 --> 00:50:33,480
Have you ever wondered

770
00:50:34,640 --> 00:50:36,080
why you don't have many friends?

771
00:50:39,840 --> 00:50:44,400
I know you speak your mind
and act on your thoughts.

772
00:50:45,400 --> 00:50:47,880
You always think of yourself as sincere.

773
00:50:48,560 --> 00:50:50,600
The people around you can feel that.

774
00:50:51,880 --> 00:50:53,960
So, your friends
don't really want to be close to you.

775
00:50:54,040 --> 00:50:55,920
Are you scolding me?

776
00:50:58,920 --> 00:51:01,160
Let's say I'm speaking with understanding.

777
00:51:02,400 --> 00:51:04,080
Because I'm just like that too.

778
00:51:04,160 --> 00:51:06,080
I'm not fake.

779
00:51:06,680 --> 00:51:08,120
You probably know that.

780
00:51:09,120 --> 00:51:12,440
I say what I think, and I do what I say.

781
00:51:12,520 --> 00:51:14,800
That's why I have to be careful
with my thoughts.

782
00:51:15,840 --> 00:51:17,360
If I think poorly,

783
00:51:18,640 --> 00:51:20,080
then I'm sure

784
00:51:21,000 --> 00:51:22,120
my actions,

785
00:51:23,440 --> 00:51:24,960
they'll be bad.

786
00:51:29,360 --> 00:51:31,160
Thank you for the coffee.

787
00:51:33,160 --> 00:51:34,480
But I don't need it.

788
00:51:36,720 --> 00:51:39,040
If Pie brought it to you,
would you want it?

789
00:51:39,120 --> 00:51:42,000
If Pie brought it
after hurting someone else,

790
00:51:42,520 --> 00:51:43,800
then I wouldn't want it.

791
00:51:46,640 --> 00:51:48,280
But I'm sure Pie wouldn't do that.

792
00:51:50,320 --> 00:51:52,320
That's why I like Pie.

793
00:51:54,680 --> 00:51:57,440
How do you like her?
What's your feeling for Pie?

794
00:51:58,120 --> 00:51:59,680
I'd like her to be my girlfriend.

795
00:52:15,080 --> 00:52:17,920
<i>How do you like her?</i>
<i>What's your feeling for Pie?</i>

796
00:52:18,480 --> 00:52:19,840
<i>I'd like her to be my girlfriend.</i>

797
00:52:37,600 --> 00:52:39,520
File, wait a second.

798
00:52:41,160 --> 00:52:42,480
Pie, just a moment.

799
00:52:43,000 --> 00:52:44,920
Left one. Okay.

800
00:52:45,000 --> 00:52:46,000
Hey.

801
00:52:46,800 --> 00:52:49,320
I need help carrying stuff
to the storage room.

802
00:52:49,400 --> 00:52:50,800
Can you help?

803
00:52:50,880 --> 00:52:52,680
- Sure.
- Thanks! Follow me.

804
00:53:02,040 --> 00:53:04,200
Can you put these in a bag for me?

805
00:53:04,280 --> 00:53:06,440
I need to quickly move the car.
If Mr. Pun comes by,

806
00:53:06,520 --> 00:53:08,880
can you tell him
I'll be up shortly to organize?

807
00:53:09,520 --> 00:53:11,720
Sure, I'll help you.

808
00:53:11,800 --> 00:53:12,840
- That would be great.
- Sure.

809
00:53:12,920 --> 00:53:14,200
- Thanks a lot.
- Right.

810
00:53:23,240 --> 00:53:25,880
I don't know how you do it,
but Pun likes you.

811
00:53:27,320 --> 00:53:29,120
Are you still obsessed with this?

812
00:53:29,840 --> 00:53:33,760
If he's why you've been bothering me,
I'll just quit right now.

813
00:53:34,560 --> 00:53:37,160
If you quit,
he will know it's because of me.

814
00:53:37,240 --> 00:53:39,400
He'll think I'm the villain
who made you quit.

815
00:53:41,360 --> 00:53:42,960
Then what do you want from me?

816
00:53:43,040 --> 00:53:45,720
I've been trying to stay out of trouble.

817
00:53:46,440 --> 00:53:49,240
I'm just here to work
and take care of my family.

818
00:53:49,840 --> 00:53:54,080
You, with everything figured out,
focusing on men, will never understand.

819
00:53:54,680 --> 00:53:56,400
Stop acting like the heroine.

820
00:53:56,480 --> 00:53:58,400
Stop pretending you don't care about Pun.

821
00:53:58,480 --> 00:54:01,520
You just approach him in a way I can't.

822
00:54:05,640 --> 00:54:06,760
Pun's a good guy.

823
00:54:06,840 --> 00:54:09,360
If he chooses you, I'll step back.

824
00:54:09,440 --> 00:54:11,160
But I won't give up.

825
00:54:12,440 --> 00:54:14,640
If you ever make him sad,

826
00:54:14,720 --> 00:54:17,600
I'll come back and laugh
at everyone you fooled.

827
00:54:18,920 --> 00:54:23,000
Even if the whole world says you're good,
I won't believe it.

828
00:54:43,600 --> 00:54:46,480
Am I a secretary or an operator now?

829
00:54:48,480 --> 00:54:49,520
Where are you going, Mink?

830
00:54:49,600 --> 00:54:50,440
Going home.

831
00:54:50,520 --> 00:54:52,400
Going home? You just started working!

832
00:54:52,480 --> 00:54:54,480
I'm quitting. I'm resigning.

833
00:54:55,400 --> 00:54:57,000
Resigning?

834
00:55:00,440 --> 00:55:01,680
I won't let you quit.

835
00:55:04,360 --> 00:55:06,520
Are you uncomfortable
with the work or personal matters?

836
00:55:08,720 --> 00:55:10,200
I'm not a good person.

837
00:55:11,240 --> 00:55:13,360
And I don't think
I can be a good employee.

838
00:55:14,120 --> 00:55:17,320
That's why I don't want to work here.

839
00:55:17,400 --> 00:55:21,160
Pie, my company isn't a monastery.

840
00:55:21,800 --> 00:55:23,680
You don't have to be flawless.

841
00:55:23,760 --> 00:55:27,720
If I chose people based on goodness,
I'd be the first one out.

842
00:55:28,320 --> 00:55:29,880
I have plenty of flaws.

843
00:55:30,520 --> 00:55:32,040
I won't let you quit, Pie.

844
00:55:33,080 --> 00:55:34,680
I want you to prove yourself.

845
00:55:37,160 --> 00:55:40,080
I've told you before,
I didn't hire you here

846
00:55:40,160 --> 00:55:41,800
for personal reasons,

847
00:55:41,880 --> 00:55:43,520
but because of your skills.

848
00:55:44,160 --> 00:55:46,920
And I believe you can do it.

849
00:55:50,360 --> 00:55:54,160
Hey, Pun was right. I agree with him.

850
00:55:54,240 --> 00:55:56,040
Don't stress about it.

851
00:55:56,120 --> 00:55:59,400
Mink's probably just upset
because he said something that upset her.

852
00:56:00,080 --> 00:56:01,320
I don't know what to do.

853
00:56:01,400 --> 00:56:03,280
I tried to talk, but she won't listen.

854
00:56:03,360 --> 00:56:06,120
Just forget it.
Let her deal with her own stuff.

855
00:56:06,200 --> 00:56:09,320
Trust me, someone like Mink
won't stay upset for long.

856
00:56:09,400 --> 00:56:11,480
She'll find a new distraction.

857
00:56:11,560 --> 00:56:13,120
Just wait and see.

858
00:56:19,480 --> 00:56:21,880
What? You're going to study in the UK?

859
00:56:21,960 --> 00:56:24,040
Yes, I've picked the course.

860
00:56:24,120 --> 00:56:25,560
I've left the papers on you desk.

861
00:56:25,640 --> 00:56:26,440
Huh?

862
00:56:26,520 --> 00:56:29,640
What about the position
Aunt Nhun helped you get with Pun?

863
00:56:30,240 --> 00:56:32,680
You're already planning to ditch it
after just one day?

864
00:56:32,760 --> 00:56:35,520
I'm not ditching,
but I've resigned already.

865
00:56:35,600 --> 00:56:36,440
What?

866
00:56:36,520 --> 00:56:38,440
You resigned? My goodness.

867
00:56:38,520 --> 00:56:40,160
Is it really that easy?

868
00:56:40,760 --> 00:56:43,520
Yeah, it wasn't the right fit,
so I didn't want to waste time.

869
00:56:44,600 --> 00:56:46,760
Good grief. What's going on?

870
00:56:46,840 --> 00:56:48,960
Quitting on the first day.

871
00:56:49,040 --> 00:56:51,960
What are you going to tell Aunt Nhun?

872
00:56:52,040 --> 00:56:54,280
Uncle, you tell her for me.

873
00:56:54,360 --> 00:56:55,800
No way!

874
00:56:55,880 --> 00:56:57,160
In a case like this,

875
00:56:57,240 --> 00:56:59,880
whoever tied the knot
should untie it themselves!

876
00:56:59,960 --> 00:57:02,840
Please, Uncle.

877
00:57:04,600 --> 00:57:06,560
Sorry, Nhun.

878
00:57:06,640 --> 00:57:10,160
I need to cancel the plan for Mink
to work with Pun.

879
00:57:10,240 --> 00:57:12,920
Well, Mink decided to resign.

880
00:57:13,960 --> 00:57:15,640
Why? What happened?

881
00:57:16,400 --> 00:57:18,040
She just started yesterday, right?

882
00:57:18,760 --> 00:57:20,280
Is she unhappy about something?

883
00:57:20,360 --> 00:57:22,560
No, it's not that.

884
00:57:22,640 --> 00:57:26,120
You see, my niece just graduated,

885
00:57:26,200 --> 00:57:29,640
and still full of drive, I wanted her
to study her master's abroad.

886
00:57:29,720 --> 00:57:33,600
But just the other day,
Mink said she wanted to work with Pun.

887
00:57:34,400 --> 00:57:36,360
Did you force her into this?

888
00:57:37,400 --> 00:57:39,800
Well, it's necessary.

889
00:57:39,880 --> 00:57:43,760
If she stays in Thailand, I fear
she'll lose her motivation to study.

890
00:57:44,360 --> 00:57:48,200
That's why I caused trouble
for you and Pun. Sorry.

891
00:57:48,280 --> 00:57:51,600
You don't have to apologize. I understand.

892
00:57:52,800 --> 00:57:53,880
But it's a shame.

893
00:57:53,960 --> 00:57:57,280
I thought our families would get closer.

894
00:57:58,360 --> 00:58:02,640
If she finishes and still wants
to work with Pun, that's fine, right?

895
00:58:06,760 --> 00:58:10,120
If she still wants to work with me,
there's no problem.

896
00:58:10,880 --> 00:58:12,120
Thank you.

897
00:58:15,640 --> 00:58:16,840
Alright.

898
00:58:18,640 --> 00:58:21,200
<i>If Pie goes to study abroad this time,</i>

899
00:58:21,280 --> 00:58:23,040
she probably won't come back.

900
00:58:23,120 --> 00:58:24,680
Pun, maybe you can change her mind.

901
00:58:24,760 --> 00:58:26,120
<i>I know she wouldn't tell</i>

902
00:58:26,200 --> 00:58:28,800
because if she did,
no one would let her go.

903
00:58:28,880 --> 00:58:30,360
I wouldn't let her go either.

904
00:58:30,440 --> 00:58:34,320
<i>I'll go back to Pie,</i>
<i>with a job, with a future.</i>

905
00:58:34,400 --> 00:58:37,920
But when you come back,
will Pie still be waiting for you?

906
00:58:38,000 --> 00:58:39,240
I don't want to waste any more time.

907
00:58:39,320 --> 00:58:40,880
<i>I want you in my life.</i>

908
00:58:40,960 --> 00:58:45,440
<i>And I believe</i>
<i>we're more than just coworkers now.</i>

909
00:58:45,520 --> 00:58:47,200
You're dating your employee?

910
00:58:47,280 --> 00:58:48,240
Pie is the one for me.

911
00:58:48,320 --> 00:58:49,520
I want to marry her.

912
00:58:49,600 --> 00:58:50,600
Huh?

913
00:58:50,680 --> 00:58:51,680
- Marry?
- Marry?

914
00:58:51,760 --> 00:58:53,040
Nhun! Nhun!

915
00:58:53,120 --> 00:58:54,560
- Nhun!
- Mom!

916
00:59:21,240 --> 00:59:24,480
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
